GAAAMMMEEE!!!

There's hit #6. The next hit should finish him.
Whoa, my groove was almost thrown off by the lag disappearing there.
Alright, so that's two white flames. Need to reach the last one now...
Welp, looks like I'll have to send my horse into the tar pit here. Bye, Yoshi!
Huh? Are we not done with Rumia yet? Find out next time! To be continued... Ze!
Demarcation (Lunatic)
Bam! Yep, the 7th hit won the battle!
Oh, I forgot to mention. If you enter as anything but small Mario or bring Yoshi, you die. Oops. Watch out for the second boss's quick rate of descent, or you're likely take damage.
Demo count: 46
So, wait... I died simply because I was big when I entered the level? What the heck, man! Why not just use the usual power up filter that's already been frequently used?
What the heck?!
Oh, wait. It works properly this time?
Push!

Demo count: 43
Hello, and welcome back to Scarlet Devil Mario! Alright, let's take on the second real level of this world-- Midnight Bird (Lunatic)!
Oh, good. The jump was still makeable. Okay, I'm gonna just quickly ludicrous speed this part...
Ah, it's the Fishin' Fish Guy! Actually, that's Rumia, and her presence made this area darker. Well, this should be much more interesting than her Hard Mode boss battle.
Glitched demo count: 4
There it is, but I gotta get Rumia to hit it!
I'm good at nailing that Piranha Plant with the Goomba, apparently.
Could only attack a dummy that time. Also, the timer is telling me to "HARRY UP" here, but since I muted the game audio, you can't hear it.
Okay, because of the absurdity of that, I'm still considering that a "glitched demo". There was no reason to force a death like that instead of using a usual power up filter.
Umm... I hope I didn't just screw myself over here by destroying a Swooper that I might've needed to make this jump.
Urchin was in my way there. If I had tried to go for that stomp, I'm sure I wouldn't have been descending fast enough, and would've died.
BGM: Contra III - Boss
Whoa there. I guess the lag helped me a bit there.
Just a 2-skull raft, since the other 2 skulls fell into the abyss when the raft first spawned.
Demo count: 45
Man, this is getting dicey...
Haw, haw!
I guess it's just those two. Okay, let's NOT intentionally hit the P-switch while standing on the brick column this time! (And don't accidentally do that either.)
I'm surprised there weren't more of those invisible troll blocks in the previous level.
Huh, one of the Torpedo Teds on the right just simply vanished. I wonder why... Did Lemmy or one of his dummies choose to occupy the same sprite slot as it?
Pfft... Well, that one was kinda my fault.
Fish, what are you doing, swimming about in midair here? Silly thing.
Thank you, lag, for making that Kaizo Chuck easier to get under!
Whoa, lucky again! Okay, where exactly are all of the invisible troll blocks here?
D'oh! If only I was descending instead of ascending when I hit that Swooper like that...
Demo count: 44
That's two hits. BTW, I wonder what the message box meant about his "quick rate of descent"? Does he go back down into his pipe faster than usual or something?
Got him that time. That's 5 hits.
I hope I wasn't supposed to quickly jump on those coins while they were blocks...
I did figure the bricks below me would act like coins after I hit the P-switch. Too bad the bricks didn't visibly change to coins when that happened.
I was wondering if I needed to quickly bounce off of that Piranha Plant to reach something, but I guess not.
I bet he's got 7 HP as well. Also, the vanilla boss music played, so I replaced it as usual.
Oh, man. Boss music.
Zwee! (I remembered to say "Zwee" this time!) Also, there's the final Yoshi coin.
Alright, that's one hit. I do know that I have to make sure I'm descending fast enough when I go for the stomp. Otherwise, I'll get hurt instead, which is cheap.
Just keep advancing at a steady pace and I should be fine.
Aw, nuts. At least that's a much fairer death than that first one, since disco shell riding, while wonky as heck, is still skill-based.
Although I guess that platform wasn't needed for anything. Why was it there then? Just to be random, or as a possible obstacle? Or, maybe a Hammer Bro. failed to spawn.
Yo, Chucks, I dare you to come onto the horizontal part of the tar!
Chuck, a tar pit isn't a good place to be playing football, you silly.
BTW, you cannot stomp these Swoopers. I had double-checked this after Ninja Boy mistakenly thought he could in one of the VLDC9 level videos he recently uploaded.

Okay, that looks like a misplaced level entrance. Argh, this could be a problem, because I don't know if I'll be able to fix it with Lunar Magic without breaking the ROM...
Well, it was an interesting battle. Way more interesting than Roy with just a bullet generator, and a buttload (126 gallons) more interesting than Hard Rumia!
And, at least Rumia here was also way more interesting than her Hard version as well!
There's hit #4. I have to keep hoping for Lemmy to appear close enough for me to attack him in time, and that the Urchin and Lava Lotus fireballs aren't in my way.
Alright, it's boss time, against Lemmy, in an underwater hazard-filled chamber!
Sonic: "You're too slow! You're too slow! You're too--" *eaten by Bulborb*
Gotta guide her into the white flames as usual.
Whoa, got lucky there! Alright, looks like I've gotta stomp a P-switch to get through here...
Whew! I was wondering for a moment if Rumia had drifted too low to hit it, since her up-and-down hovering got thrown off slightly when she hit the previous flames.
Yes, I finally remembered to include the Super Meat Boy "WAAARRRPPP ZOOONNNEEE!!!" sound bite there! ...Oh, boy... It's the Swooper death ceiling.
I just had to do that for hahas.
Just a tiny iota too late that time.
Whoa, I'm glad I jumped on that fish when I did, to reach this platform!
There's a bunch of misguided Chucks here.
...Yep!

Hit #3, but of course it's not over yet. At least the enemies in this room are easy enough to avoid. I bet they would still be fairly easy to dodge even without the lag.
